properties.areaDesc: Central Carbon County; Upper North Platte River Basin
properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued February 16 at 8:17AM MST until February 17 at 8:00PM MST by NWS Cheyenne WY
properties.description:
...SIGNIFICANT MOUNTAIN SNOWFALL EXPECTED THROUGH MONDAY...

* WHAT...Snow and blowing snow. Total snow accumulations of 2 to
6 inches. Winds gusting as high as 60 mph.

* WHERE...Central Carbon County and Upper North Platte River
Basin including Rawlins and Saratoga.

* WHEN...Through 8 PM MST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Slick roads and reduced visibility. The hazardous
conditions will impact the morning and evening commute.
Blowing snow will reduce visibility at times.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 8 PM MST MONDAY
